 spatula. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour, up to overnight."},{"content":"Place marinated chicken into mixing bowl, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and cook <b><b>15 min\/212°F\/\/speed 1<b><b>, then shred <b>5 sec\/\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Remove lid, insert simmering basket and strain juices. Transfer chicken to a bowl and serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until ready to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve as a sandwich between potato buns with sliced red onion.","Habanero chilies are hot; use caution when handling.","Marinate whole chicken thighs overnight and grill instead of cooking and shredding in Thermomix.","Jerk Chicken Mayonnaise: after straining, reserve cooking liquid, transfer chicken to a separate bowl and set aside. Return cooking liquid to mixing bowl, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and cook <b>40 min\/212°F\/speed 3<b>. Transfer reduced juices (approx. 2.5 oz) to a bowl and combine with 1 tbsp mayonnaise."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 55m","4 portions"]}